  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Maturation (April 2026)</h2>
    <p>
      Release infrastructure, the shared design system, and downstream
      consumption pipelines are deployed across the ecosystem. ATX-1 evolves
      toward MITRE-style alignment.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>2026-04-09</strong> — <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-governance/releases/tag/atx-1-v2.2">ATX-1 v2.2</a> published.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2026-04-12</strong> — Ecosystem-wide release pipeline deployed:
        CalVer dev-log tagging on every push, nightly rollup, monthly release
        across all five public Astro sites.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2026-04-13</strong> — Cross-language structural normalization
        initiative opened
        (<a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-initiative/issues/30">aegis-initiative#30</a>);
        new-feature-work freeze takes effect ecosystem-wide until the
        normalization ships.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2026-04-25</strong> — Research site
        <a href="https://aegis-labs.dev">aegis-labs.dev</a> goes live.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2026-04-26</strong> — ATX-1 v2.3 published with severity field
        removed for MITRE-style alignment; aegis-docs.com begins fetching the
        ATX-1 specification from
        <a href="https://aegis-governance.com">aegis-governance.com</a> at
        build time, establishing a single source of truth for the threat
        matrix.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2026-05-29</strong> — ATX-1 v2.4 adds Termination Poisoning
        (T6003) and 10 sub-techniques, mapped to the strategies of Xu et al.
        (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.05846">LoopTrap</a>); inclusion
        endorsed by the authors. Live on
        <a href="https://aegis-governance.com">aegis-governance.com</a>;
        Zenodo / IEEE DataPort deposit pending.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Verifiability</h2>
    <p>
      All dates above are derived from public Git history or external
      registries. Release tags can be verified at the linked GitHub releases.
      DOIs are minted via Zenodo and resolve to permanent records that include
      the deposited content. The internal detailed roadmap, which tracks
      forward-looking work and architectural decisions, is canonical in the
      <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis">aegis governance repository</a>;
      the public-facing roadmap is rendered at
      <a href="/ecosystem/roadmap/">/ecosystem/roadmap/</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocLayout>
